OL,6,FKingspan was one of seven firms
OL,7,Fcriticised in the Grenfell Inquiry
OL,8,Freport and could face being banned
OL,9,Ffrom public contracts as the
OL,10,FGovernment pledged to bring change in
OL,11,Fthe wake of the fatal fire.
OL,13,FDeputy Prime Minister Angela Rayner,
OL,14,Fcriticised some firms' "disgraceful
OL,15,Fmercenary behaviour (which) put profit
OL,16,Fbefore people and exploited the
OL,17,Fregulatory regime to evade
OL,18,Faccountability with fatal
OL,19,Fconsequences".
